data.text: @PatriciaTreble Lucky I'm from the UK and live in the UK so, i'll be awake anyway :-)
@PatriciaTreble Even earlier than that if the're on the West coast

Royal wedding update,  5/5: The last glimpse the public will have of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle will be that evening, when they leave Windsor Castle for nearby Frogmore House for a night of festivities. https://t.co/RVTPvtKVKa

Royal wedding update,  4/5: Then, as close family members watch, the newlyweds get into a royal carriage for a short drive through Windsor. And they mean short: It's just 25 minutes long. https://t.co/FGP8WWc6hC
Royal wedding update,  3/5: After the wedding, Prince Harry and Meghan Markle will "acknowledge" the 200 representatives of his charities gathered outside the chapel. https://t.co/vPnhd03Plr

Royal wedding update,  2/5: North American viewers will have to get up EARLY to see all the action. Wedding guests start arriving at St. George's chapel at 9:30 am (4:30 am ET) https://t.co/MUHgRqfUHS
